  "title": "I could not find what I was looking for",
  "body": "Hi! I have a documentation issue on InstantSearch.js, I could not find what I was looking for which is: \r\n\r\nI have built a custom widget using your guide. I am using a multiple select list using jquery. I am trying to refine the search results with multiple values but I am not sure how to feed the values back. Your documentation only shows how to feed a single variable. Here is a sample of what I am trying to do:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nconst refine = renderParams.refine;\r\n$(container).find('select').on('change', function(event) {\r\n     //array of selected options\r\n     var selectedOptions = $(container).find('select').val();\r\n     //sending array to algolia\r\n     refine(selectedOptions);\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nThanks,\r\nJoe\r\n",
